<br>
But *if*, and only *if* a member of Awakened Souls did start this thread, I can easily understand why.<br>
<br>
I've seem some good people wear the guildtag of &lt;Awakened Souls&gt; and I've always believed they were in the guild because they were hoping to build something good and great.  Note the key word, &quot;Build.&quot;  I'm talking about people who have been on this server from day one and have scratched their way to where they are now, earning it by the bubble.  Now they are in their mid 50s maybe, and in a major raiding guild, and they figure they've earned their spurs.  Until someone with their credit card (or their parents') buys a level 60 toon (and I never use the word &quot;toon&quot;, not when it's really someone's character) and steps ahead of them in line.  Ahead for position, responsibility, importance in the guild, and yes, even loot.  Which does matter to some people.<br>
<br>
I think it's damaging not only to the fabric of the game, but also to the inner wellness of a guild, to move in Ebayed characters like this.  They have no history, no context.  And if the members of a guild mean nothing, then the guild means nothing.<br>
<br>
Saga has a level 52 warrior.  Her name is Mixxi Moondreamer.  She shows up at most of the raids and major events.  I group with her every Sunday.  She's our Queen Tank, for what that's worth.  Level 52, with about 900 ac and 2200 hit points.  I know that without checking.<br>
<br>
Not much of a tank, as major raids go, perhaps.  But when I line up behind her I know that's SAGA.  And that's what it's all about folks.  I'd rather raid Crushbone with people I know and care about to give the experience meaning, than go to the planes with companions who were bought and paid for.<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
Saga<br>
